FBIS3-60856 "jptot001__l94104" JPRS-TOT-94-001-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 7 January 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA RUSSIA Four Caucasians Kidnap Children; No Motive Given Ministry Asks Tehran To Ensure Hostages' Safety LD2412174293 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1503 GMT 24 Dec 93 LD2412174293 Moscow INTERFAX Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] In connection with the recent seizure of hostages, Russia's Foreign Ministry sent a note to Tehran, requesting it to ensure the safety of hostages, if the terrorists insist on flying to Iran. INTERFAX learned this from the director of the ministry's Press and Information Department, Grigoriy Karasin. According to him, every possible channel has been used for contacts with the Iranian authorities. "For example, the ministry's note will be forwarded not only to Iran's Foreign Ministry, but also to the Iranian ambassadors in Moscow and Baku," he said.
